Text Parser (src/utils/resumeParser.ts)
Pure regex-based, no deps. ~200 lines. Detects:
1. Contact: email regex, phone regex, LinkedIn URL, first non-empty lines as name
2. Summary: first paragraph after contact, before first section header
3. Sections by headers: "EXPERIENCE", "EDUCATION", "SKILLS", "PROJECTS", etc.
4. Experience block:
   - Job Title → Company | Location | Dates (pattern: "Title\nCompany | Loc | Date")
   - Lines after as bullets
5. Education: "Degree - School, Year" or "School, Degree (Year)"
6. Skills: comma-separated or line-separated after "Skills" header
Outputs a partial ResumeData object. Unparseable sections are left as empty arrays.
Data Normalizer (src/utils/resumeNormalizer.ts)
Runs after any import (JSON, text, PDF) to:
- Fill missing optional fields with []
- Add crypto.randomUUID() to items missing id
- Ensure contact has all required fields (fill empty strings)
- Returns a complete, valid ResumeData
